<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E6CC523FF6FBB96FA4AE8CC" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="key">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E6CC523FF6FBB96FD23E9F4" blockId="110.[151,757,1157,1183]" box="[151,757,1157,1183]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FF6FBB96FD23E9F4" bold="true" box="[151,757,1157,1183]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FE95BB96FD8AE9F4" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[365,604,1157,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FE95BB96FE2AE9F4" bold="true" box="[365,508,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
using males
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E6CC523FF6FBBD6FA4AE99C" blockId="110.[151,1436,1221,1447]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
1. Hind femora not swollen or curved (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E6CC523FDC6BBD6FD15E9B1" box="[574,707,1221,1242]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="109.[151,263,1767,1790]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-116@109.[151,1436,193,1746]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Pyrophanes spp. 221, 222 P. appendiculata (slides, USNM). 223, 224 Luciola venusta type male (MNHN). 225, 226 P. quadrimaculata type female (MNHN). 227 Luciola semilimbata type female (MNHN). 221 male, 222 female abdomens; 223, 225 dorsal; 224 ventral; 226 type labels. Figure legends: 1 anterior projection of aedeagal sheath sternite; 2 basal piece aedeagus; 3 lateral area anterior prolongation of T8; 4 posterior area of aedeagal sheath in region of paraprocts; 5 ventrolateral surface of T8 in spined area; 6 posterolateral area of T8; 7 anterior plates bursa; 8 posterior plates bursa; 9 median oviduct plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265424/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Figs 223, 224</figureCitation>
)................................ 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FBA1BBD6FAFEE9B1" authority="(Olivier)" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1113,1320,1221,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilimbata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FBA1BBD6FB18E9B1" box="[1113,1230,1221,1242]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">semilimbata</emphasis>
(Olivier)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FAD6BBD6FA4AE9B1" bold="true" box="[1326,1436,1221,1242]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="458122695E6CC523FAD6BBD6FA4AE9B1" box="[1326,1436,1221,1242]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Hind femora swollen and curved......................................................................... 2
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E6CC523FF6FBBECFA4AE859" blockId="110.[151,1436,1221,1447]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
2. Elytra medium to dark brown, often with lateral and sutural margins semitransparent and pale (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E6CC523FB88BBECFB23E87F" box="[1136,1269,1279,1300]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="109.[151,263,1767,1790]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-116@109.[151,1436,193,1746]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Pyrophanes spp. 221, 222 P. appendiculata (slides, USNM). 223, 224 Luciola venusta type male (MNHN). 225, 226 P. quadrimaculata type female (MNHN). 227 Luciola semilimbata type female (MNHN). 221 male, 222 female abdomens; 223, 225 dorsal; 224 ventral; 226 type labels. Figure legends: 1 anterior projection of aedeagal sheath sternite; 2 basal piece aedeagus; 3 lateral area anterior prolongation of T8; 4 posterior area of aedeagal sheath in region of paraprocts; 5 ventrolateral surface of T8 in spined area; 6 posterolateral area of T8; 7 anterior plates bursa; 8 posterior plates bursa; 9 median oviduct plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265424/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Figs 223, 224</figureCitation>
)............ 3 Elytra dingy or pale, clear yellow, always with apex dark brown to black; base of elytra may be brown (
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E6CC523FB3ABA0EFAC2E859" box="[1218,1300,1309,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="109.[151,263,1767,1790]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-116@109.[151,1436,193,1746]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Pyrophanes spp. 221, 222 P. appendiculata (slides, USNM). 223, 224 Luciola venusta type male (MNHN). 225, 226 P. quadrimaculata type female (MNHN). 227 Luciola semilimbata type female (MNHN). 221 male, 222 female abdomens; 223, 225 dorsal; 224 ventral; 226 type labels. Figure legends: 1 anterior projection of aedeagal sheath sternite; 2 basal piece aedeagus; 3 lateral area anterior prolongation of T8; 4 posterior area of aedeagal sheath in region of paraprocts; 5 ventrolateral surface of T8 in spined area; 6 posterolateral area of T8; 7 anterior plates bursa; 8 posterior plates bursa; 9 median oviduct plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265424/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Fig. 225</figureCitation>
)......... 4
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E6CC523FF6FBA29FA4AE807" blockId="110.[151,1436,1221,1447]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
3 Elytra medium to dark brown, lateral margin, and often also sutural margin, yellow................ 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FB31BA29FECAE807" authority="Olivier Elytra" authorityName="Olivier Elytra" genus="Pyr" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="appendiculata">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FB31BA29FA84E824" box="[1225,1362,1338,1359]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">appendiculata</emphasis>
Olivier Elytra
</taxonomicName>
medium to dark brown, without any paler margins.......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FAFBBA4BFA4AE807" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[1283,1436,1367,1389]" genus="Pyro" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="beccarii">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FAFBBA4BFA84E806" box="[1283,1362,1368,1389]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">beccarii</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E6CC523FF6FBA66FA4AE8CC" blockId="110.[151,1436,1221,1447]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
4 Elytra yellow with apical and basal dark markings......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FB41BA66FECAE8CC" authority="Olivier Elytra" authorityName="Olivier Elytra" genus="Pyro" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FB41BA66FA84E8E1" box="[1209,1362,1397,1418]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">quadrimaculata</emphasis>
Olivier Elytra
</taxonomicName>
yellow with only apices dark brown...................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FAEBBA81FA4AE8CC" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[1299,1436,1426,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FAEBBA81FA84E8CC" box="[1299,1362,1426,1447]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">similis</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E6CC523FF3FBADEFE99EB8A" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E6CC523FF3FBADEFE99EB8A" blockId="110.[151,1440,1485,1761]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FF3FBADEFEE2E88E" bold="true" box="[199,308,1485,1509]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E6CC523FEBDBADEFE3CE88E" author="Olivier, E." box="[325,490,1485,1509]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="333 - 374" refId="ref128538" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FD81BADEFC50E88E" authority="Motsch." authorityName="Motsch." box="[633,902,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FD81BADEFCF6E88E" box="[633,800,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Luciola indica</emphasis>
Motsch.
</taxonomicName>
approached 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FBE4BADEFB7EE88E" box="[1052,1192,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FBE4BADEFB72E88E" box="[1052,1188,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pyrophanes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and (1902) formally incorporated it. This species does not belong in 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FD22BAE2FC88EB62" box="[730,862,1521,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FD22BAE2FC88EB62" box="[730,862,1521,1545]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is being addressed (Boontop, Lambkin and Ballantyne in prep.). Certain diagrams of the terminal abdomen of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FC6DB906FBCCEB46" box="[917,1050,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FC6DB906FBCCEB46" box="[917,1050,1557,1581]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are inaccurate e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E6CC523FB03B906FA41EB46" author="Olivier, E." box="[1275,1431,1557,1581]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="333 - 374" refId="ref128538" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885</bibRefCitation>
, Plate V, 
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E6CC523FEFBB92AFE9AEB3A" box="[259,332,1593,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–17" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-85@39.[151,1436,265,1935]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 9–17. Australoluciola anthracina type male, Cyclops (MNHN). 9, 10 dorsal (9) and ventral; 11 V6, 7 ventral; 12 pronotum dorsal; 13 type labels; 14 aedeagal sheath ventral; 15-17 aedeagus, dorsal (15), ventral (16) and lateral. These figures share scale lines: 15–17." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265360/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Fig.12</figureCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E6CC523FE61B92AFDE1EB3A" author="Olivier, E." box="[409,567,1593,1617]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref128760" refString="Olivier, E. (1907) Coleoptera, Lampyridae. Genera Insectorum, 53, 1 - 74 [Luciolinae, 48 - 56]." type="journal article" year="1907">Olivier (1907</bibRefCitation>
Plate 3 
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E6CC523FD5FB92AFD29EB3A" box="[679,767,1593,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–17" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-85@39.[151,1436,265,1935]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 9–17. Australoluciola anthracina type male, Cyclops (MNHN). 9, 10 dorsal (9) and ventral; 11 V6, 7 ventral; 12 pronotum dorsal; 13 type labels; 14 aedeagal sheath ventral; 15-17 aedeagus, dorsal (15), ventral (16) and lateral. These figures share scale lines: 15–17." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265360/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) are inaccurate representations of the terminal ventrite; 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E6CC523FF6FB94EFE57EB1E" author="McDermott, F. A." box="[151,385,1629,1653]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref127702" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1964) The taxonomy of the Lampyridae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 90, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1964">McDermott’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
brief redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FD72B94EFCD8EB1E" box="[650,782,1629,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FD72B94EFCD8EB1E" box="[650,782,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was probably influenced by the atypical abdomen of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FA7FB94DFE5AEBF2" authority="McLean" authorityName="McLean" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macdermotti">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FA7FB94DFEF2EBF2" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">P. macdermotti</emphasis>
McLean
</taxonomicName>
which he is known to have examined at this time and he misinterpreted various aspects. Ballantyne in 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E6CC523FEC2B9B6FE0CEBD6" author="Calder, A. A." box="[314,474,1701,1725]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" refId="ref123793" refString="Calder, A. A. (1998) Coleoptera: Elateroidea In Wells, A. (ed.) Zoological Catalogue of Australia, 29.6 (CSIRO Publishing Melbourne)." type="book" year="1998">Calder (1998)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FD7AB9B6FC45EBD6" authority="Lea" authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1921" box="[642,915,1701,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FD7AB9B6FC88EBD6" box="[642,862,1701,1725]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Luciola complicata</emphasis>
Lea
</taxonomicName>
from far north 
<collectingRegion id="AE028DE25E6CC523FBB5B9B6FB07EBD6" box="[1101,1233,1701,1725]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Queensland</collectingRegion>
with 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E6CC523FAEFB9B6FE99EB8A" authority="Olivier." authorityName="Olivier." class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beccarii">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E6CC523FAEFB9B6FF25EB8A" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes beccarii</emphasis>
Olivier.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
